.TH "RTCINBOUNDRTPSTREAMSTATS.NACKCOUNT" "3JS" "August 15, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
RTCInboundRtpStreamStats.nackCount \- RTCInboundRtpStreamStats:
nackCount property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]nackCount\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]RTCInboundRtpStreamStats\f[R] dictionary indicates the number of
times the receiver sent a \f[B]NACK\f[R] packet to the sender.
.PP
A NACK (Negative ACKnowledgement, also called \(lqGeneric NACK\(rq)
packet tells the sender that one or more of the RTP packets it sent were
lost in transport.
.SH VALUE
A positive integer.
